library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)

Which volcanoes are likely to cause the most damage if they blow?

volcano_deaths %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = deaths, colour=vei)) +
  geom_point(size=3.5, 
             alpha = 1, 
             shape = 18) +   
  scale_colour_manual(values =  c("0" = "khaki", "1" = "gold1", "2" = "darkgoldenrod2",
          "3" = "darkorange2", "4" = "firebrick1", "5" = "firebrick", "6" = "firebrick4",
          "7" = "black")) +
  labs(
      x = "Year of eruption",
      y = "Number of deaths",
      title = "Number of Deaths Caused by Volanoes",
      subtitle = "(Some estimates)"
      ) +
    theme(panel.background = element_rect(fill = "slategray2"))

volcano_deaths %>% 
  filter(year>1820) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = deaths, colour=vei)) +
  geom_point(size=3.5, 
             alpha = 1, 
             shape = 18) +   
  scale_colour_manual(values =  c("0" = "khaki", "1" = "gold1", "2" = "darkgoldenrod2",
          "3" = "darkorange2", "4" = "firebrick1", "5" = "firebrick", "6" = "firebrick4",
          "7" = "black")) +
  labs(
      x = "Year of eruption",
      y = "Number of deaths",
      title = "Number of Deaths Caused by Volanoes",
      subtitle = "(after 1820)"
      ) +
    theme(panel.background = element_rect(fill = "slategray2"))

ggplot(data = world) +
  geom_sf(data = tectonic_plates,
          colour = "slateblue4") +
  geom_sf(color = "gray68", fill = "ivory") +
  ggtitle("Size of the population within 100km of volanoes",
          subtitle = "Top 10 highlighted") +
  geom_point(
    data = volcanoes,
    aes(x = longitude, y = latitude, 
        color = primary_volcano_type,
        size=population_within_100_km),
    alpha = 0.5
  ) +
    theme(legend.position = "none") +
  geom_jitter(
     data = popn_1mn_plus,
     colour = "firebrick4",
     shape = 24,
     fill = "firebrick4",
     size =2, 
     aes(longitude, latitude)
      ) 

ggplot(data = world) +
  geom_sf(data = tectonic_plates,
          colour = "slateblue4") +
  geom_sf(color = "gray68", fill = "ivory") +
  ggtitle("VEI of the Last Volcanic Eruptions") +
  geom_point(
    data = eruptions_vei,
    aes(x = longitude, y = latitude, 
        color = vei,
        alpha = 0.5)) +
  scale_colour_manual(values =  c("0" = "khaki", "1" = "gold1", "2" = "darkgoldenrod2",
          "3" = "darkorange2", "4" = "firebrick1", "5" = "firebrick", "6" = "firebrick4",
          "7" = "black")) +
  guides(alpha = "none")
